\ Comprehensive save-image / load-image round-trip. Covers, in one image:
\ definitions with a cross-reference, a variable, a symbol, a pair-valued
\ variable, a logic var bound to a value, a pair that shares a bound logic var,
\ and a data stack holding a set, a string, a matrix, and a nested frame (frame
\ + sub-frame + set). Save, clobber the live interpreter, load, verify all of it.

: square dup * ;
: cube dup square * ;
: bump-all [> x | x 1 + :] map ;
variable counter   42 to counter
symbol red
variable lst   [( 1 2 3 null )] to lst
variable V     lvar to V   V 42 ~ drop
variable pr     lvar to X   [( X X null )] to pr   X 9 ~ drop
variable seg   3 double-segment to seg   seg 0 1.5 !i drop   seg 1 2.5 !i drop   seg 2 3.5 !i drop

\ stack state to round-trip
< 1 2 3 >
"hello"
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix
{ :a 1 :b { :c 2 } :d < 7 8 > }

"/tmp/lf-image-test.image" save-image

\ scribble over live state
clear
: square 0 ;
0 to counter
3 square . cr            \ 0  (clobbered)

"/tmp/lf-image-test.image" load-image

\ definitions + cross-reference restored
3 square . cr            \ 9
3 cube . cr              \ 27
\ scalar / symbol / pair / lvar variables restored
counter . cr             \ 42
red . cr                 \ red
lst . cr                 \ [( 1 2 3 null )]
V . cr                   \ 42
pr . cr                   \ [( 9 9 null )]   shared lvar binding survived
seg size . cr            \ 3   segment length survived
seg 1 @i . cr            \ 2.5 segment contents survived
\ a loaded quotation executes, disassembles (header classified from the
\ persisted span), and faults with the same trace on native and wasm
[ 1 2 3 ] bump-all . cr  \ [ 2 3 4 ]
' bump-all see-compiled
[ null ] bump-all        \ (error: null 1 + inside the loaded quotation)
\ stack restored (frame on top): nested frame + set fields
dup /a @ . cr            \ 1
dup /b/c @ . cr          \ 2   nested frame survived
dup /d @ size . cr       \ 2   nested set survived
.s cr                    \ < 1 2 3 >  hello  <matrix 2x2 ...>  { ... }

bye
